Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need
to peel!). Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with
@oil{}, then season with half of the @Cajun Spice Mix{1%portion}, @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your
oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(halved and thinly sliced).
Halve the @green pepper{1}(halved and sliced into thin strips) and discard the core
and seeds. Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}(zested and halved). Peel and grate the
@garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Put the
@king prawns{150%g} in a #small bowl{} along with the remaining Cajun spice and
lime zest, mix and set aside to marinate. Drain and rinse the @cannellini beans{1}(drained and rinsed) in a #sieve{}.

Put the sliced pepper and onion on a baking tray. Drizzle over some @oil{}, season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}, toss together, then spread in a single layer. Roast on
the middle shelf of your oven until the onion has softened and the pepper is starting
to char, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a small bowl combine the @mayonnaise{1}(mayo) and half of the lime
juice. Mix well to form a pourable consistency. Add a bit more lime juice if needed.

Once the onion and pepper are cooked, heat a splash of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} over
a medium-high heat. When hot, add the roasted pepper and onion along with the garlic
and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add the @tomato puree{30%g}, @water{100%ml}, @sugar{} and
@vegetable stock powder{1%portion}. Stir in the beans and simmer until thickened,
~{3-5%minutes}. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then remove from the heat.

Meanwhile, heat a splash of @oil{} in a large frying pan over high heat. When hot,
add the prawns, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir-fry until cooked through,
~{3-5%minutes}.

> The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Once everything is cooked, divide your wedges between plates. Reheat the beans if
necessary and spoon them alongside the wedges. Top with the prawns and drizzle the
lime mayo all over. Enjoy!